Brazil Probably Won’t Take Currency Measures, iG Says

-- B y   R o b i n   S t r i n g e r
-- 
2011-04-01T14:35:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/brazil-probably-won-t-take-currency-measures-ig-says-correct-.html
(Corrects to say real appreciation in first paragraph of
story published March 31.)  The Brazilian government probably
won’t take new measures to stem the real’s appreciation, said
columnist Guilherme Barros, of news website iG.  Brazil  is more worried about inflation than foreign
exchange rates, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
